mixture for reconstitution of the receptor-gating function. When
phosphatidylethanolamine was replaced totally or partially by other
phospholipids with the same or different acyl chain composition,
a marked decrease of ion transport was apparent, even when similar
vesicle size, receptor incorporation, and agonist-induced affinity
transitions were obtained. Therefore, the maintenance of the affinity
state transitions of the reconstituted receptor is a necessary but
not sufficient condition for the manifestation of the ion-gating
