which binds at the picrotoxinin site on the GABA(A) receptors and
blocks the behavioral actions of ethanol, also dose-dependently reversed
the anti-conflict effect of this neurosteroid. The results suggest
that allopregnanolone may be working either at a site specific for
the benzodiazepine receptor inverse agonist RO15-4513 or at the picrotoxinin
site to produce its potent anxiolytic-like behavioral effects.},
