of those parts of a membrane protein that are located in the lipid
headgroup region. A number of examples are given where the conformation
of the headgroup-embedded region of a membrane protein changes during
the reaction cycle of the protein; activities of such proteins might
be expected to be particularly sensitive to lipid headgroup structure.
