state for structural features of the sterol molecule was found. The
molecular requirements differ both from those postulated for sterol-phospholipid
interactions and from those known to be necessary for the functional
activity of other proteins. The different behavior of both peptide
receptors concerning the cholesterol dependence of their ligand binding
