and initiates the rotational movements associated with opening of
the channel. Both vestibules of the channel are strongly electronegative,
providing a cation-stabilising environment at either entrance of
the membrane pore. Access to the pore on the intracellular side is
further influenced by narrow lateral windows, which would be expected
to screen out electrostatically ions of the wrong charge and size.},
