depletion without phospholipid back exchange or fusion. The incubation
of membranes with excess liposomes could only achieve about a 50{\%}
reduction in the molar ratio of cholesterol to phospholipid. In no
case was the number of cholesterol molecules per AChR oligomer reduced
below 36. The remaining cholesterol could not be depleted either
by longer incubations or by multiple, sequential depletions. Cholesterol
depletion was accompanied by a significant increase in bulk membrane
fluidity as measured by electron spin resonance spectroscopy, but
the equilibrium binding parameters of acetylcholine to its receptor
were unaltered. This suggests strongly that there exist two pools
