these interactions during events associated with signal transduction
by electron spin resonance spectroscopy (ESR) using spin-labeled
analogues of phospholipids, androstane, and stearic acid. Protein-lipid
interactions were characterized in receptor-rich membranes prepared
from Torpedo californica electric tissue preserving the native lipid
environment of the nAChR. We found a strong preference of the receptor
