anesthesia might arise because of interactions at molecular sites
near the interface of neuronal membranes with the aqueous environment
and, therefore, might require increased concentrations of anesthetic
molecules at membrane interfaces. As an initial test of this hypothesis,
we calculated in molecular dynamics simulations the free energy profiles
for the transfer of anesthetic 1,1,2-trifluoroethane and nonanesthetic
