but not perfluoroethane, exhibits a free energy minimum and, therefore,
increased concentrations at both interfaces. The transfer of trifluoroethane
from water to the nonpolar hexane or interior of the membrane is
accompanied by a considerable, solvent-induced shift in the conformational
