monovalent cations, characteristics that resemble the conduction
properties of the cation-selective branch of the family that includes
acetylcholine and serotonin receptors. Here we present the X-ray
structure of GLIC at 3.1 A resolution. The structure reveals a conformation
of the channel that is distinct from ELIC and that probably resembles
the open state. In combination, both structures suggest a novel gating
mechanism for pentameric ligand-gated ion channels where channel
opening proceeds by a change in the tilt of the pore-forming helices.},
