temperature dependent, and the results are discussed in terms of
exchange between mobile and perturbed environments. Plots of the
mobile/perturbed ratios vs. lipid/protein ratios at 1 degree C gave
straight lines from which the relative binding affinity of each spin-label
and the number of perturbed lipids per receptor protein could be
