W15 side chains at the center of the dimeric hydrophobic core, with
the possibility of two additional minor binding sites between the
F12 and F52 ring stacks of each monomer. The high-resolution structure
of the designed anesthetic-binding protein offers unprecedented atomistic
details about possible sites for anesthetic-protein interactions
that are essential to the understanding of molecular mechanisms of
