more extensively identify photolabeled GABA(A)R amino acids. [³H]TDBzl-etomidate
photolabeled in an etomidate-inhibitable manner $\beta$3Val-290, in the
$\beta$3M3 transmembrane helix, as well as $\alpha$1Met-236 in $\alpha$1M1, a residue
photolabeled by [³H]azietomidate, while no photolabeling of amino
acids in the $\alpha$M2 and $\beta$M2 helices that also border the etomidate binding
site was detected. The location of these photolabeled amino acids
in GABA(A)R homology models derived from the recently determined
