potent inhibitors of [(3)H]ivermectin binding in rat brain. However,
the rank order for anticonvulsant activity did not parallel the rank
order for affinity at the [(3)H]ivermectin site and it was reasoned
that avermectins may have differential affinity or efficacy at subtypes
of the GABA(A) receptor. All the active compounds tested potentiated
the effects of GABA at recombinant GABA(A) receptors in oocytes and
